botkubehelp to find more information about the supported As suggested in help message, to execute kubectl commands, send message in following format in the channel where BotKube is already added or as a direct message to <kubectl command without `kubectl` prefix [--cluster-name <cluster_name ] Run Kubectl commands Run < kubectl command without kubectl prefix to get kubectl response from the cluster configured with the This command needs to be executed from configured channel else use --cluster-name flag described Specify cluster name If you have installed BotKube backend on multiple clusters, you can pass --cluster-name flag to execute kubectl command on specific To get the list of all clusters configured in botkube, you can use the ping For response, use --cluster-name flag to specify the cluster’s name on which command needs to be Use of this flag allows you to get response from any channel or group where BotKube is The flag is ignored in notifier commands as they can be executed from the configured channel See Examples for the use Check BotKube health Run ping to the channel where BotKube is The BotKube will respond you with the PONG message from all the configured Use --cluster-name flag to get response from the cluster mentioned in the Else check the deployment in Kubernetes cluster in the botkube Managing notifications Depending upon your configuration, you will receive notifications about Kubernetes resources lifecycle events and their BotKube bot allows you to enable disable notifications only from the configured Run botkubehelp , the bot will reply with the help message about the supported message View BotKube configuration Run notifier showconfig message from the configured channel where BotKube is The bot will reply you with the configuration with which the controller is If you wish to change the configuration, you can update config section in helm botkube values.yaml and then run helm upgrade . $ helm upgrade botkube \ --set =<CLUSTER_NAME \ --set =<ALLOW_KUBECTL \ helm botkube OR You can also modify the controller configuration at You have to edit the configmap which will also restart the BotKube pod to update mounted configuration in the $ kubectl edit configmap botkube This command will open configmap specs in vim Do the required changes, save and The BotKube pod will automatically restart to have these configuration in Disable notifications If you want to stop receiving notifications from BotKube, run notifier stop from the configured channel where BotKube is You will no longer receive notifications from the BotKube Enable notifications If you want to receice notifications from BotKube again, run notifier start from the configured channel where BotKube is Check notifier status Run notifier status to check status of notifier if running or stopped from the configured Manage filters BotKube allows you to manage filters using commands List available filters Run filters list to get list of available filters and their running status Disable filter Run filters disable filter-name to disable perticular filter to skip checks on resource specs Enable filter Run filters enable filter-name to enable perticular filter to run checks on resource specs Filter events using Annotations Using Annotations, it is possible - to make BotKube ignore events on a specific resource Send notification about specific resource to different channel and the configured one Ignore events Annotation disable: true disables event notifications for the annotated Send notification to channel Annotation channel: <channel_name sends events notifications of the annotated object to the mentioned Make sure that you have added BotKube in the channel you want to send notification in   ElasticSearch :: Messaging bot for monitoring and What does it do? THC or tetrahydrocannabinol is the most potent analgesic in medical It is responsible for the intoxicating or euphoric effects, traditionally associated with marijuana Although research has discovered a vast amount of potent healthcare benefits for THC, the combination of CBD to offset some of the psychoactive effect of THC is currently becoming more common in medical marijuana Who Qualifies for Medical Marijuana in Florida? Seal is an electronic notary public platform service that allows consumers and businesses to complete the notarization process entirely Is Seal legal in my state? Seal is a remote electronic notary public platform that enables Texas notaries, as authorized by Texas law, to notarize documents for use in Texas and in states across the Every state provides legal authority for recognition and acceptance of common notarizations, including those from How is Seal legal? In July , the State of Texas passed Gov’t Code §406.008(b) which allows appropriately certified Texas notaries to serve customers And, these notaries were given the explicit authority to serve Americans no matter where they re These online notarizations are accepted across the country due to the Full Faith and Credit Clause of the United States Constitution and state laws that specifically address and accept out of state How does Seal work? Seal is an electronic notary public platform and software service offered to clients via any desktop or laptop with a Seal’s service enables a meeting with a notary, just like meeting with a traditional notary public , but the meeting takes place entirely You simply register on the Seal website, then upload your document(s) and verify your You verify your identity using authentication, which offers you a series of specific questions that only you can Once your ID has been verified, your identity is further validated using a photo You are then connected with a commissioned Texas Electronic Notary Public via live The notary public confirms your identity visually using the scanned photo ID, and then witnesses as you electronically sign the Our notary then completes the electronic notarization process using digital Once complete, you will receive detailed instructions on how to access your notarized document You can choose to print and deliver it or send it electronically to whomever you would The whole process is completed in In accordance with the Texas statutes governing electronic notarization, all video calls are recorded so that any authorized party may verify your electronic How much does it cost to notarize a document? $25 per each Notary Seal +$6 –– For each signers +$1 –– For each additional signature per signer Please note that we do offer discounted pricing based on If you’d like to explore volume pricing, please email What Documents we DO NOT NOTARIZE? • Wills, codicils, and trusts • Documents for use in Iowa • Motor vehicle title transfers and odometer • • Our notaries cannot perform marriage ceremonies • Our notaries cannot certify true copies of birth, marriage, death certificates or court Can you notarize a document that isn’t written in English? Not at this Please follow the following steps to translate into English: ) Go to and have the document ) Upload the translated form to Lets Get Can Marriage certificates, Birth or Death certificates be notarized? Texas notaries are NOT authorized to notarize and certify true copies of these documents at this Can I notarize an ? We do not notarize forms at this Can I notarize a document for use outside the United States? The Answer is No… When a notarized document is intended for use in another country, the notary’s commission and current status must typically be certified by his or her Secretary of What are the acceptable forms of ID that I can use on Seal? Acceptable forms of ID include the following photo IDs if valid and unexpired: • State Issued Driver’s License • State Issued Photo ID • Passport Book • Passport Card • Certificate of US citizenship • Certificate of Naturalization • Foreign Passport • Alien Registration Card with Photo What type of payments are accepted? We accept all major credit cards and Stripe and SEAL SERVICES AVAILABLE ANY TIME, ANYWHERE! WE’RE OPEN 7. & Resources Press Reports Stories Get Involved Requests for Proposals Jobs Contact Us Map MAP Giga maps schools and their connectivity levels, creating a display of access and No one knows how many there are total in the world (we estimate there are million) and this map is vital to funders, governments, and for Giga uses machine learning to scan satellite images and identify These are then marked by coloured dots on an map: green where there is good connectivity amber where it is limited and red where there is no connectivity at With help from its partners, Giga has now mapped the location of over 1 million schools and has connectivity data for nearly one third of VIEW MAPS OF SCHOOL CONNECTIVITY HOW MAPPING HELPS US CONNECT SCHOOLS In Colombia, we applied artificial intelligence techniques to automatically map schools from satellite imagery and provide the government the location of 7,000 schools that were not part of their official Mapping shows where resources are Many governments do not know where all the schools in their countries Without that information, they – and other nongovernmental organizations – cannot effectively provide services or deliver resources to children and their During emergencies, this information can also guide response efforts by informing how to deliver critical information and other It shows where there is internet and if it is Many governments and organizations are committed to connecting schools to the internet, but do not yet have the ability to monitor whether schools are actually connected and whether connections are of good It improves access to data for It has been proven that availability and quality of data is considerably higher for wealthier This data inequity leads to disparities in resource allocation, where vulnerable populations are left It highlights gaps in Without knowing where connectivity needs to be extended, governments and investors don’t know how much it will cost, making it more difficult and riskier to It establishes market Because internet service providers cannot measure the size of potential new customers, they struggle to make a case for bringing infrastructure to remote This results in limited investment and increased HOW HAS MAPPING HELPED COUNTRIES SO FAR? Kyrgyzstan Giga has helped the Government of Kyrgyzstan to generate $200k savings per year (40% of its education connectivity budget). By seeing all the schools on a map and their corresponding connectivity, the Government was able to renegotiate contracts and subsequently reduce prices by almost half (from $50 month to $28.5 month) and to almost double speeds (from to ).
